task.summary: Default task
Refactored more packaging Removed incomplete javadocs in some classes
Refactord LocationHandler to Locations Refactored PlayerHandler to Players Updated Inventories
Added method to get uuid

Added debug mode for players Updated BlockData to be a wrapper for blocks Added command for debug mode Added Permission Enum Added Debugger to handle messages for debug mode Updated Worlds, Commons, and Blocks to have new methods for manipulation
Added new hasItem method for players added new containsItem method for inventories
Updated worlds module
Began migrating database to an actual structure (https://docs.google.com/drawings/d/1rmxOQKbiuug3cxWOMalgt-Ajb-CYIztuLmXia167vpc)

Renamed the plugin from Tunnels-Common to Commons
Added an additional plugin.yml for a no-commands build of Commons

Renamed the plugin from Tunnels-Common to Commons
Added an additional plugin.yml for a no-commands build of Commons
Modified all of the database structure Updated and optimized many of the commands Added more utilities and tools for the classes
Added tasks package to threading for runnables added methods in entities to get entities near a location Added debugger to it's own package. made debuggeractions for 'unit testing' commons
Fixed critical bug with player data not being syncd Fixed bugs with ban and unban Created debug entry for time handler

Created permissions package Updated version to 1.3 Fixed parsing bug fixed banning bug began permissions system implementation began permissiable extension refactored some command and their permissions
Moved helpmenus class into menus moved itemformat and pagedisplay enum to own class, not nested
Addition to previous commit, files were missing in the commit
Added table creation statements Added method in commonUtils to parse uuid strings
Removed the NPC package- To difficult to maintain and utilizes to much NMS FOAR ME
New Item Menu API Updated config names Removed NPC node from config Inventory listeners for the custom item-menus Warp config being added, warp menu is a work-in-progress
New Item Menu API Updated config names Removed NPC node from config Inventory listeners for the custom item-menus Warp config being added, warp menu is a work-in-progress

Made serializable objects for ItemStacks and Enchantment (XmlItemStack and XmlEnchantment) Created debug units for item serialization and de-serialization Created invalidEnchantment exception Updated items with methods to determine if an item is a weapon or armor
Added field for stack amount

Created item rename command New methods to spawn lit tnt, drop players inventory, and other arbitrary methods.
Array utils with fisher-yates shuffle

Updated configuration to have some setters (for use in configuration menu) Began working on in-game config menu(still unfinished, but will be finished soon) Added class holding materialdatas for different colours of wool Added string scroller

Added check so that if a player has others hidden, their particles won't be displayed.
Formatting color codes in itemmenu and menu items
Moved colorcode from config/formatting to config
Fixed bug with speed in playerWrapper

Added equals method to blockdata Added support for exclamation points in the letter class Added the BlockText command, used to write text with blocks Added XmlSound to allow serialization of sounds New exception for when an invalid material name is given Began working on the ExtraItems class, used to get the items with data-values easily
Added support for cardinal and compass directions Better block regeneration methods Updates to block-text A whole shitload more!

New XmlInventory to serialize inventories new package for gadgets (gadgets, items with effect / performers) new event GadgetUseEvent NameTagEntity in entities.nms, invisible nameless bat!
Interfaces for gadgets and abstracted implementations.
Began working on Admin menu
Made entire new core for plugin writing, handling alot of the boiler plating when using commons to it's fullest. This includes a sort of "game" api where minigames, bukkit plugins, and games in general can be made so much easier.
extending MiniGame gives you a plugin base with all the tools required, all you do is register the gamestates and away she goes!
BukkitPlugin is rather bare bones, but, it's supposed to be.
CraftGame is a BukkitPlugin but with implementation of the GameCore
All interfaces are available so creating your own cores and implementing them is encouraged!
Began writing arena managment, player wrappers, and other things to ease development.
Implemented ID Command Fixed issued in Gadgets ArenaManager, Handler, and Arena classes updated to be aware of themselves.

Removed permissions from TunnelsXP Command Added serializable potion effect equivelant Updated entities class with methods to pull, push, heal, and remove entities Fixed issue in items class with null-pointer-exception when calling hasMetaData
Renamed PlayerWrapper to MinecraftPlayer Updated minigames arena API with more methods for handling cycling, less errors, and more.
Renamed TickCooldown to PlayerTicker Created Ticker interface Created BasicTicker class for invocation-call-amount tracking 2 new utility classes: HashUtils and ListUtils More messages addedd to Messages

August 21'st ================
Additions --------- - CreatureBuilder class, a builder class to easily spawn and customize creatures - ArmorInventory class, a wrapper around EntityEquipment, used in conjunction with Entities / Players to easily assign equipment. - ArmorBuilder class, a builder interface for the ArmorInventory wrapper. - Added registerDebugActions method to BukkitPlugin class - Added some Javadocs to Players - Created DebugCreatureBuilder - Created DebugArmorBuilder
Reductions --------- - Removed EntityArmorSlot and moved calls globally to ArmorSlot
August 20'th ================
Additions --------- - Javadocs for Entities class & methods
Notes --------- - renamed Entities.spawnRainbowSheep to spawnRandomSheep
August 18'th, 2014 ================
Additions --------- - Added messages for actions regarding arenas (Loading, adding, etc)
Notes --------- - Chanded the addArena method in ArenaHandler to return a boolean.
August 14'th, 2014 ==================
Additions --------- - Added 'filterCollection' method to Entities - Added 'reduceCollection' method to Entities - Added 'selectEntitiesNearLocation' method to Entities - Added 'selectLivingEntitiesNearLocation' method to Entities - Added 'setHotbarSelection' method to Players - Added 'setHotbarItem' method to Players - Added 'setHotbarContents' method to Players
Reductions --------- - Removed 'getHandle' method from Entities - Removed 'setPositionRotation' method from Entities - Removed 'addEntity' method from Entities - Removed 'invokeProjectile' method from Entities - Removed 'getBukkitEntity' method from Entities
Notes ---------
- I deprecated Items.makeItem(Material, String, String...) as it wouldn't compile due to how var-args work. - Moved 'registerGadgets' method from Subclass MiniGame to super-class BukkitPlugin - Removed deprication on Sounds.playSoundForPlayersAtLocation

August 26'th ================
Additions ----------- - Documented block & chat package along with all classes in each - Documented ColorCode class - Documented all Xml Wrapper classes (XmlEnchantment, XmlInventory, XmlItemStack, XmlLocation, XmlMenuItem, XmlPotionEffects, XmlSound) - Documented cuboid package and all contained classes. - Documented Debugger and DebugAction - Documented effect package and all contained classes. - Documented entity package and all contained classes. - Created two ban methods in Players: ban(Player, Punishment) and ban(String, Punishment) - Documented Players class - Added ItemMessage to BukkitPlugin for plugins to use. - Added debug method and logger creation to BukkitPlugin
Reductions ----------- - Removed the 'packet' package - Remove the 'disguise' package - Removed the 'Action' class from event package. - Renamed the DataHandler class to TextFile - Moved the Tag class to be nested inside TextFile - Removed debug method from static context - Removed executors and handlers from static-view in Commons
Notes ----------- - Moved the ChestType class from block.chest.ChestType to block.ChestType - Refactored the ban command to use the new Players.ban(String / Player, Punishment)
August 25th ================
Additions --------- - Added the clear(Player) method to PlayerTicker - Created LimitedGadget class, which is a gadget limited by it's amount of uses - Added the remove(Inventory, ItemStack) method to Inventories - Added the removeItem(Player, ItemStack) method to Players - Added the hasGadget(Player, Gadget) method to Players
Notes --------- - Moved the Game API from commons.plugin.game to commons.game for Commons 1.5
August 22nd ================
Additions --------- - Created Cuboids class, with basic world-edit like functionality. - Made cuboid class serializable from an xml interface - Created block replace data object, which holds information about block manipulation. (What chance a block has to be replaced when using it in an action).
Reductions ---------
Notes --------- - Refactored ItemBuilder to have a much simpler naming scheme.
August 21'st ================
Additions --------- - CreatureBuilder class, a builder class to easily spawn and customize creatures - ArmorInventory class, a wrapper around EntityEquipment, used in conjunction with Entities / Players to easily assign equipment. - ArmorBuilder class, a builder interface for the ArmorInventory wrapper. - Added registerDebugActions method to BukkitPlugin class - Added some Javadocs to Players - Created DebugCreatureBuilder - Created DebugArmorBuilder
Reductions --------- - Removed EntityArmorSlot and moved calls globally to ArmorSlot
August 20'th ================
Additions --------- - Javadocs for Entities class & methods
Notes --------- - renamed Entities.spawnRainbowSheep to spawnRandomSheep

View change-log.md for all details.
Added vectors package, for further development with vectors and various vector-related calculations
Created PropertiesItem and PropertiesBuilder interfaces, implementation currently incomplete.
Wrote Guns API, with any item able to be used as a projectile
Wrote properties for guns, all serializable.
Wrote events for bullet-hit-block and bullet-hit-entity
Created event for when guns are fired
Created the Fish cannon weapon
Made interfaces containing actions, will be later utilized for more extendable functionality.

FishCannon is no longer buggy.
Updated BlockHitAction and CreatureHitAction to take a player arg, the player performing the action.
Created serializable ParticleEffect (base)
Moved BaseGun to game.guns
Created BulletProperties class, moving attributes of ammunition away from the gun-class, so guns can (potentially) use multiple ammunition's, etc.
Created FancyBullet class which trails bullets with particles, currently untested.
Fixed Bug in ItemBuilder, where lore on items isn't colored.

September 23'rd, 2014: + Created the PreTeleportLocation extension to regular locations. Can be used as a Location as it's derived from that. + Created the BaseLocation class + Added options to /fw. - /fw <amount> <delay> ~ Cleaned up code for potion Command, wrote idea for menu to create potions.~ Cleaned up Recipe command, saved 10 lines. ~ Cleaned up hat command code, saved 5 lines. ~ Fully implemented permissions for the /back feature. ~ Fixed the Recipes not being Shown ~ Fixed /buypremium and /removepremium not working. ~ Reduced complexity of logic in the UpdatePlayerPremiumCallable
September 22'nd, 2014: ~ Added permissions to using the /back command ~ Updated /armor command to use the new ArmorSet enum for set-searching.
September 20'th, 2014: ~ Fixed the leather-armor array in Items.java; Everything should appear in the right slot now. ~ Began Writing documentation for all the commands and permissions. + Created a player death listener to set the pre-teleport-location when they die.
September 18'th, 2014: ~ Updated updateOnlineStatus method in ServerDatabaseConnector to insert default statuses if there's no existing data for them. ~
September 17'th, 2014: + Added checks to CommandPreProcessListener to see if the player's using a disabled command. + Added disablePluginsCommand to commandConfig + Added disableBukkitCommands to commandConfig + Created the UpdatedOnlineStatusThread to perform the status-update for players. ~ Updated PlayerJoinEvent to set players status in the online-status database table ~ Updated PlayerQuitEvent and PlayerKickEvent to toggle players status in the online-status table. - Deleted and removed all code for ItemMenuConfiguration - Removed XmlItemMenu (used in ItemMenuConfiguration)

Entirely new command library, allows removal of most boiler plate coding :)
Updated all the commands to use this new library
Created Weapon interface
created cyclicpotion, used to randomize the duration and amp of a potion
Prepping for Commons 1.7
Prepping for commons 1.7

Moved the UserManager from MiniGame to CraftGame Allowed GameConnectionListener to accept a craftgame instance, so both minigames and full-fledged games can be registered.
Updated XmlItemstack to serialize the owner of player skulls, if the item is a player skull.
Created method inside Items to verify whether or not an item is a player skull.

Created the TitleBuilder class Moved methods related to world-wide entity removal from Entities, to Worlds
Created the ArenaLoadEvent Updated ArenaCycleEvent to instance the game it was created from.
Moved Connection class in http package to public view Created CommonPlugin interface Made BukkitPlugin implement the CommonPlugin interface.
Updated to Commons 1.7.4
Prepping to merge into 1.8-Commons
Moved Commons to Update 1.8.1

Bug fixes on the Item handlers Updated database statements to no longer have bugs with servers selection Finished the soundData, soundPlayer, and sounds over-haul; More to come with patch 1.8.2 Added an option in config to disable fall damage
Refer to log.txt for updates to do with 1.8.2 (Commons)
Revisions in detail in Log.txt- Febuary 15'th & 20'th
Refer to log.txt (Build 1.8.4)
Refer to log.txt (Build 1.8.5)
Refer to log.txt (Build 1.8.5)
Slight bit more documentation!
Todo's for the inventory menu system overhaul
